Third-party attribution: filter-chain conversion table (src/included/modules/filter_chain.py)

The `filter_chain_rce` module adapts the conversion-chain algorithm and the
base64-character-to-iconv-gadget lookup table from:

    php_filter_chain_generator
    https://github.com/synacktiv/php_filter_chain_generator
    Copyright Synacktiv

That upstream project does not carry a LICENSE file; under default copyright
rules its code is "all rights reserved" by its authors, with no explicit
license grant. It is, however, published research shared openly for security
testing purposes and is widely referenced and reused in the security
community (e.g. HackTricks and numerous other public writeups cite and
reproduce the same technique and table).

We use the table and algorithm here with explicit attribution (in the module
docstring and this file), for the same authorized-security-testing purpose
the original work was published for. We have not sought or received an
explicit license grant from Synacktiv. If you are a Synacktiv maintainer and
would like this handled differently (removal, a specific license, or
different attribution), please open an issue on this repository.

Independently reimplementing the underlying research (re-deriving the
conversion table from scratch via the same brute-force search over iconv
character sets) remains an option if a fully independent implementation is
ever required.
